      <hedline>
        <hl1>Media, New and Old</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Jane Pollak letter on Sept 21 article on wireless e-mail device</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>As I read excerpts to my husband from the article about the BlackBerry, a wireless e-mail device (''E-Mail You Can't Outrun,'' Sept. 21), I wasn't getting any kind of response. When I perceived that he was tuning me out, I looked up to find him interacting with a communications tool that by comparison has reached antique status. He was huddled over and completely absorbed in reading the front page of the newspaper.</p>
        <p>JANE POLLAK  Westport, Conn.</p>
      </block>
